among Logicians, the firft <a class="xref" href="../1771/vol3.html#article-MODE">mode</a> of the firft <a class="xref" href="../1842/vol9.html#article-FIGURE">figure</a> of syllogifms. A syllogifm in barbara is one whereof all the proportions are univerfal and <a class="xref" href="../1842/vol2.html#article-AFFIRMATIVE">affirmative</a>; the middle <a class="xref" href="../1842/vol21.html#article-TERM">term</a> being the fubject of the firft proposition, and <a class="xref" href="../1778/vol2.html#article-ATTRIBUTE">attribute</a> in the <a class="xref" href="../1842/vol20.html#article-SECOND">second</a>.

*Examp.* <a class="xref" href="vol3.html#article-BAR">Bar</a>. Every wicked <a class="xref" href="../1842/vol14.html#article-MAN">man</a> is miserable;
Ba. All tyrants are wicked men;
Ra. Therefore all tyrants are miserable.
